In London Rover said that the relationship with Honda would continue into  the next century.
It said in a statement that "agreement has been reached with Honda on all  current collaborative projects" and that "terms have been agreed which provide  a satisfactory outcome for both companies."
Rover Group managing director John Towers said: "We are delighted that our  negotiations have reached a successful conclusion. Rover Group has greatly  valued the relationship with Honda, and we are very pleased indeed that it  will continue to the benefit of both companies in the years ahead."
